lines.text: The last snowflake once fell on my nose
Now flying backwards to last winter
I realize that hellos are goodbyes
The moment I softly let go of your hand
Wings of fruit, trembling branches
A soul for soul bound to soar
To the very edge of the staring ocean
If and if I mean to fall apart
I will decide where you are for all time
Above all years
May your path be clear
May you get aware
Dreams are all crystallized
Sweet, please, crack a little smile
You and me alone
In this world you've chosen as your own
Don't worry, I'm well aware
That there's no free smell in the end
Witches sigh on one little palm spring
So I'll dance, flamboyantly into that good night land
Bold voyage, may your path be clear
May you get aware, dreams are all crystallized
Please, crack a little smile
You'll be alone in this world you've chosen
As your own
It's such a dancing way to get yourself
Spend my whole life unraveling
And though it might cost me everything I have
I never regret, wouldn't have been any other way
Cause those two trees don't lie on their lonely road
We'll find their destination, see the cosmos
Me, I'd like to see this world with snow
For the most beautiful thing ever happened to me
Thank you.
